The paper deals with image scrambling using Sudoku associated two-dimensional bijections. This involves the use of matrix element representations and bijective mappings, which are concepts related to cryptography and information theory (cs.CR and cs.IT). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision techniques (cs.CV), as well as mathematical modeling and optimization (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for image scrambling, which can be considered a graphics-related problem (cs.GR).
